), completely covering the head from above, fore margin with 5+5 distinct, subequal, faintly incised, rounded lobulations, middle with 4+4 distinct tubercles (
Fig. 2B
). Dorsum strongly convex, paraterga lying below mid-body height, moderately sloping down at about 20–25°. Tegument covered with a microspiculate cerotegument. Postcollum paraterga thick and rather indistinctly lobulated laterally (
Fig. 2B, E
), three lobulations on 2 
nd
and pore-bearing rings, 
vs
two lobes on poreless ones (
